$ /proc/$pid/mem

This file allows to access the → Linux/memory[memory] of the → Linux/kernel/process[process] with process id (PID) = `$pid` using standard `read` and `write` operations *if* one has the
necessary rights to do so.

sa:
  → Linux/memory/read-write-another-processes-memory[Read and write] another → Linux/kernel/process[process's] → Linux/memory.

 `→ Linux/fhs/proc/pid`
